00:37:58.390 --> 00:38:00.670
so along with the task of
documenting the devastation

00:38:00.670 --> 00:38:07.890
of Hiroshima there was a second
goal, the data was to be compiled

00:38:07.890 --> 00:38:12.170
to be used to help America to
survive a nuclear attack at home.

00:38:12.170 --> 00:38:14.110
So here's the paradox.

00:38:14.110 --> 00:38:18.360
At the moment of America's total
victory there was simultaneously an

00:38:18.360 --> 00:38:23.180
awareness of the culture of the
country's future vulnerability

00:38:23.180 --> 00:38:26.610
so the way out of that paradox
lay in the concrete structures

00:38:26.610 --> 00:38:28.260
that had survived the blast.

00:38:28.260 --> 00:38:31.610
In the words of The Survey
men arriving at Hiroshima

00:38:31.610 --> 00:38:35.290
and Nagasaki had been
constantly impressed by the shells

00:38:35.290 --> 00:38:39.150
of reinforced concrete
buildings that still are rising

00:38:39.150 --> 00:38:42.990
above the rubble of brick and stone
or the ashes of wooden buildings.

00:38:42.990 --> 00:38:46.420
The Physical Damage Division
studied those concrete shells

00:38:46.420 --> 00:38:49.430
as if they were blueprints
for the atomic future.

00:38:49.430 --> 00:38:53.670 position:56%
