00:41:00.540 --> 00:41:08.730 position:56%
The fire. On the night of January 7,
1967, Corsbee's daughter had a date.

00:41:08.730 --> 00:41:10.820
She was newly divorced
and she was planning

00:41:10.820 --> 00:41:14.130
on dropping her nine-year-old
daughter off at her father's house

00:41:14.130 --> 00:41:16.570
but at the last minute
her date canceled

00:41:16.570 --> 00:41:19.380
and she decided to stay at home.

00:41:19.380 --> 00:41:21.630
Early the next morning
the phone rang.

00:41:21.630 --> 00:41:24.980
There had been a fire
at her father's house.

00:41:24.980 --> 00:41:29.300
Corsbee's house was a nine bedroom
tutor mansion called Homewood

00:41:29.300 --> 00:41:31.350
in Ossining, New York.

00:41:31.350 --> 00:41:35.150
When Nancy and her daughter arrived
they were confronted by a house

00:41:35.150 --> 00:41:37.490
that was totally devastated.

00:41:37.490 --> 00:41:42.360
About 200 volunteer firefighters,
four pumper trucks and a hook

00:41:42.360 --> 00:41:46.830
and ladder had been called to
fight the blaze but to no avail.

00:41:46.830 --> 00:41:49.130
Robert Corsbee, his wife Evelyn

00:41:49.130 --> 00:41:52.390
and their 22-year-old son
had all died in the blaze.

00:41:52.390 --> 00:41:54.830
The first assistant fire chief

00:41:54.830 --> 00:41:58.010
at the time was a man named
Richard Apostalico [phonetic].

00:41:58.010 --> 00:42:01.810
Forty-four years later he
still remembered the fire.

00:42:01.810 --> 00:42:04.030
It was one of the worst
I'd ever seen.

00:42:04.030 --> 00:42:07.020
Some things you never forget.

00:42:07.020 --> 00:42:10.190 position:56%
The house was built like a fortress.

00:42:10.190 --> 00:42:15.340
It had extra slate thick
roofs and the windows

00:42:15.340 --> 00:42:17.940
where at least one
quarter of an inch thick.

00:42:17.940 --> 00:42:21.160
We had a terrible time doing
what we call ventilation.

00:42:21.160 --> 00:42:24.680
That's how you let the gases and
burning fumes out of a building.

00:42:24.680 --> 00:42:26.670
It was something unreal.

00:42:26.670 --> 00:42:30.040
We had pipe poles and we still
couldn't break the glass.

00:42:30.040 --> 00:42:34.070 position:56%
As a result of the unusual
construction the house contained the

00:42:34.070 --> 00:42:37.190
fire like a furnace.

00:42:37.190 --> 00:42:40.540
Apostalico found Mrs.
Corsbee in the foyer

00:42:40.540 --> 00:42:43.150
